msgSnippet: For Australian English you could try: http://www.ling.mq.edu.au/speech/phonetics/topics.html http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_English www.fonetiks.org
messageBody:
For Australian English you could try:
 
http://www.ling.mq.edu.au/speech/phonetics/topics.html
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_English
www.fonetiks.org
http://dictionary.cambridge.org
http://reese.linguist.de/English/australia.htm
The Macquarie Dictionary (hard copy or on-line)
The Astralian Modern Oxford Dictionary
http://www.ling.mq.edu.au/speech/phonetics/phonetics/ausenglish/
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_English_phonology
http://www.ling.mq.edu.au/speech/phonetics/phonetics/ausenglish/impressionistic.html
or Google "Strine".
 
Here one for NZ ponunciation;
http://faculty.washington.edu/dillon/PhonResources/kiwisounds/NewZealandPronunciation.html
 
You could also try the resources @:
http://web.usc.es/~iadimly/prophonetics.htm
 
Hope this helps.
 
B. J.
